  <steps>
    <step num="0">Mix cream cheese, and sugar. Mix in the egg, vanilla extract, and cinnamon. </step>
    <step num="1">Hollow the apple with a melon baller. </step>
    <step num="2">Fill ⅔ of hollowed apple with cream cheese mixture. </step>
    <step num="3">Bake 25-30 minutes at 176˚C (350˚F). </step>
    <step num="4">For maple pecan sauce, boil whipping cream and maple syrup until thick. Stir in pecans just before serving. </step>
    <step num="5">Serve with crushed graham cracker (optional) and maple pecans sauce. </step>
    <step num="6">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
